<span class="displaytext"><i>excerpts from: "bauer urges 'open mind'" in the washington times</i> <p><i> by ralph z. hallow </i> </p><p><i> october 13, 2007 </i> </p><p>social conservative leader gary l. bauer has issued an appeal to supporters to consider former sen. (candidate full)'s bid for the (PARTY NAME) presidential nomination. </p><p>"i hope pro-family, pro-life christians will continue to keep an open mind about senator (candidate last)'s candidacy..." mr. bauer wrote in an e-mail addressed to supporters. "a (candidate last) vs. hillary [(candidate last)] race would be an easy call for me to make." </p><p>... </p><p>mr. bauer and family research council president tony perkins said that while mr. (candidate last) is not a regular churchgoer, neither was ronald reagan, an icon of the religious right. </p><p>... </p><p>in his e-mail yesterday, mr. bauer noted that mr. (candidate last) "has ... repeatedly said that [supreme court abortion ruling] roe v. wade ought to be overturned, calling it 'bad law and bad medicine.' " </p><p><i> to view the entire article, please visit </i> <a href="http://www.washingtontimes.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?aid=/20071013/nation/110130037/1001"> http://www.washingtontimes.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?aid=/20071013/nation/110130037/1001 </a></p></span>



